1. *Vampir* me je ujeo sinoć. (A vampire bit me last night.)
2. Njegove oči su bile crvene kao kod *vampira*. (His eyes were as red as those of a vampire.)
3. *Vampirski* mitovi postoje u svim kulturama sveta. (Vampiric myths exist in all cultures of the world.)
4. Ona voli da gleda filmove o *vampirima*. (She likes to watch movies about vampires.)
5. Čuli su neobične zvukove iz grobnice i pomislili da je tamo *vampir*. (They heard strange sounds from the tomb and thought there was a vampire there.)
6. *Vampiru* je bilo teško da se suzdrži od krvi. (The vampire had a hard time restraining himself from blood.)
7. Ljudi su u prošlosti verovali da ako stavite beli luk na vrata, *vampiri* neće ući. (In the past, people believed that if you put garlic on your doors, vampires wouldn't come in.)
8. *Vampirima* se obično pripisuju natprirodne moći. (Vampires are usually attributed with supernatural powers.)
9. Iako je odlučila da se ne boji, osećala se kao da je u *vampirskoj* priči. (Although she decided not to be afraid, she felt like she was in a vampire story.)
10. Iako je krenula u potragu za *vampirom*, nije bila spremna na ono što je zatekla. (Although she set out to search for a vampire, she wasn't prepared for what she found.)